File: Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng. JOHANNESBURG - Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng intends to appeal the Judicial Conduct Committee ruling that he apologise for his pro-Israel comments. During a webinar hosted by The Jerusalem Post last year, he cited Biblical references to justify his comments. Africa 4 Palestine, SA Boycott Disinvestments and Sanctions Coalition and Women's CulturalGroup, laid complaints about Mogoeng's comments. READ: Forum calls for Chief Justice Mogoeng to step aside They argued Mogoeng's remarks contravened the judicial ethical rules. A statement released by the Judicial Conduct Committee says a date for the appeal is yet to be set, and will be heard by at least three of its members.